The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, February 27, 2004 Life -The Cal GuideThe Cal GuideDrive inIf you are an outdoors kind of a person, Drive Inn might just be the place to drop in for a meal or even a snack or two. At this 2,000-sq ft outdoor restaurant on Middleton Street (a stones throw from the Jeevan Deep building), you can roll up your sleeves and dig into a wide variety of Chinese, Continental and Indian delicacies, all the while being surrounded by lots of greenery. The restaurant, which has been around for almost 10 years now, also has arrangements for those who prefer air-conditioned comfort and families can dine in the privacy of quaint air-conditioned cottages, if they so choose. Whats more, if you are into cars, Drive Inn is the only place in town where you can get yourself a new pair of wheels while munching away to glory. The eatery doubles up as a car-buying, selling and financing outlet.  Drive Inn, which is a pure vegetarian restaurant, offers all kinds of spicy rolls with different fillings as well as a variety of Chinese soups and noodle preparations. For a slice of Tibet, foodies can dig into the momos and thukpas that are also available here. Also on offer is a Chinese combo meal, which is very reasonably priced at Rs 68. overs of the tandoor, there is Paneer Seekh Kebab, Paneer Chalky, Paneer Tikka, Vegetarian Seekh Kebab, Tandoori Salad, Paneer Kulcha and Masala Kulcha. Other popular Indian dishes such as Dal Makhani, Paneer Butter Masala, Benarasi Alu Dum, Navratna Korma and Chana Masala also find a place on the menu. Enjoy these with anything from khasta roti and butter roti to butter naan, kabuli naan and paneer kulcha naan. To round off the meal, you can choose between raita, papad, lassi and ice-cream. If youre in the mood for smaller bites, opt for the French fries, pizzas, burgers, gratins and sandwiches or go Indian with a range of pakoras and chaats.  Drive Inn is open throughout the week and undertakes free home and office delivery upto five kms. Address: 10, Middleton Street, Calcutta  71 Phone: 2229 2409/ 2229 9492.
